					 <h1 id="target-user">Summary<br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /></h1>
					 <p class="primary-users-bit">Mirror is a very big clothing store chain for both kids and adults. They also have different styles--casual, business, sporty, party, and formal. You have been contacted by Mirror to help them take their business online since currently they only have a very outdated informational website that only lists locations, promotions, and a bit of background about the company. They don’t want to keep anything that they currently have, so it’s all up to you. For now, they want to start with a new logo and an e-commerce responsive website where they can sell their products online.</p>
					
					 <br /> 
					 <p class="primary-goals">Through the process of developing this site, it was discovered that users want an easy to use resource for shopping. Many of them found shopping online to be difficult and shied away from it, mostly because it couldn’t match the real-time experience in terms of understanding the feedback. That became the main mission of the site: maximum info for the user.</p>
					 
