				<div class="margins-div">
					 <p class=" primary-users-bit">With all this research and useful information from users, there were several personas that could have been chosen. The best thing to do then was to look at the clusters of charateristics from each of them to develop a unifying persona. Here is what came out: </p>
					 <br /> 
				<%= image_tag('ngoc-persona.png', class: 'img-fluid', :style => 'box-shadow: 0px 3px 15px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);') %> <br /> <br /> 
				<%= image_tag('ngoc-empathy.png', class: 'img-fluid', :style => 'box-shadow: 0px 3px 15px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);') %> <br /> <br /> 
					<p class=" primary-users-bit"> From there, we began to think through two objectives: how to gamify the experience as well as how the navigation of such an experience would work. In that case, we made the navigation for it very robust so that the user could easily revert back to common points in the application while still making it easy to jump to other actvities when needed.  With this solution, we’ve included choosing an avatar as part of the onboarding process. From here, users could easily view their friends and challenge them as needed. </p> <br /> 

